{
  "stem": "23438.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But they didn't want to decide his future, as a baby.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They decided to let him grow up and make a decision by himself.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Well, he was never eventually given the chance to do that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But because they wanted to give him a free hand, they didn't circumcise him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] Which could have helped him to survive, but didn't, due to the circumstances.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Out of my paternal family, I'm the only survivor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "There's nobody else left.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The older uncle perished during the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "The younger one survived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Him and my grandmother were sheltered by Jadwiga's family, in the country.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Grandma died there, peacefully in her sleep.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And Roman, after the war, married Jadwiga Giegiecka.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "They lived like two lovebirds for a number of years afterwards.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But it was too late for them to have any children anyway.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "My maternal family was quite extensive.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "I never knew the grandfather.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "He died some years before I was born.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "He was, apparently, quite a wealthy merchant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "My grandmother had five children, four girls and one boy.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "The girls were all very good-looking, and very strong women.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "There is, in the family of my grandmother, the Markson family, a tradition of tough, strong women.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "The one boy was not quite such a success.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "The eldest daughter, Anna, finished medical studies after World War I.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "She was a doctor.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "She married a doctor and lived in [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Lodz. ?] The second daughter, [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Helen, ?] was my mother.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "She had two children, my brother and myself.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "She almost completed chemistry studies in [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "Kharkiv. ?] But she was too heavily pregnant with my brother to sit for final exams.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And she never, never, ever worked in this area.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "The third daughter, Maria, [?",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
